                <h3>GTPL</h3>
                <p>GTPL is a Gujarat-based cable TV and broadband provider with a meaningful presence across the state. They offer broadband starting around ₹499/month alongside cable TV services. Their technology in smaller towns may still be HFC (hybrid fibre-coaxial) rather than pure FTTH, which limits peak speeds compared to pure fiber.</p>
                <p>GTPL is a competitor to Nisan in the cable TV space specifically, and some Bilimora residents have existing GTPL cable TV connections. Their broadband coverage in Bilimora West is partial.</p>
                <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Customers already on GTPL cable TV who want to add internet on the same provider relationship.</p>

                <h3>BSNL</h3>
                <p>BSNL remains the government-owned fallback option and is available in most of Bilimora through copper telephone lines. Their actual speeds in practice are typically 2–15 Mbps — far below what fiber delivers — and their infrastructure has not been significantly upgraded in years. Support operates on government office hours and can involve multiple visits to the local exchange office.</p>
                <p>BSNL's plans may appear affordable at ₹449/month at the entry level, but the effective speed per rupee is far lower than any fiber option.</p>
                <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Rural addresses where no fiber provider has coverage, or customers who specifically require a landline telephone line bundled with their connection.</p>

